# .dockerignore for the Plonter MongoDB clone container.
#
# WHY IT LIVES AT THE REPO ROOT (not in deploy/): Docker only honors the
# .dockerignore at the *build context* root. The Render blueprint + the documented
# build command both use the repo root as context, so this file MUST sit here to
# (a) keep the real MONGO_URI secret out of every build, and (b) trim the large
# repo down to just what the image needs. A companion reference copy is kept at
# deploy/dockerignore.reference for discoverability.
#
# Strategy: exclude everything, then re-include only the paths the Dockerfile COPYs,
# then re-exclude secrets/data that live inside those paths.

# 1) Exclude everything by default.
*

# 2) Re-include exactly what the image needs.
!api/
!mongo_adapter/
!vendor/
!composer.json
!composer.lock
!sharing/content_api.php
!sharing/content_share_api.php
!sharing/auth_common.php
!media_api.php
!clone/
!deploy/

# 3) Re-exclude secrets, real data, and junk that may sit inside the re-included dirs.
# Secret connection string — must NEVER enter the build context / image.
.mongo_uri
**/.mongo_uri
# SQLite leftovers (app now uses MongoDB) — do not ship real data.
**/*.db
# Locally-stored media blobs (real content; warehouse data lives in Mongo/host fs).
api/vocab_audio_blobs/
# The clone must NOT carry its own api/ (empty DBs that could wipe real data) or tests.
clone/api/
clone/tests/
# VCS / OS / editor noise.
**/.git
**/.gitignore
**/.DS_Store
**/._*
**/node_modules/
**/*.log
